                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16384543" author="jwagenleitner" created="Sat, 3 Mar 2018 07:50:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is related to the change for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8325&quot; title=&quot;@CompileStatic calls wrong newInstance method.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8325&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8325&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/d965023c2668991e744c213c5125c5adcc677cd9&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;commit d965023c266899&lt;/a&gt;.&#160;Looks like the change restricts the comparison of the primitive (number) types and their wrappers. Before the change it was valid to pass a &lt;tt&gt;BigDecimal&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;BigInteger&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;(or even an &lt;tt&gt;AtomicLong&lt;/tt&gt;)&#160;to a method taking a &lt;tt&gt;short&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the test case provided the &lt;tt&gt;1.0&lt;/tt&gt; is a &lt;tt&gt;BigDecimal&lt;/tt&gt;, the method call works if &lt;tt&gt;1.0f&lt;/tt&gt; is used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16513732" author="emilles" created="Fri, 15 Jun 2018 12:06:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to follow up, we used to be able to pass literals like &lt;tt&gt;1.0&lt;/tt&gt; to methods taking a double and it would be converted automatically.  Now we must use &lt;tt&gt;1.0d&lt;/tt&gt; or else face a compile error under &lt;tt&gt;@CompileStatic&lt;/tt&gt;.  Is the error the new expected behavior?  If so, I&apos;ll close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16592743" author="daniel_sun" created="Sun, 26 Aug 2018 01:50:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is better to convert type automatically IMO. The issue is a bit similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6668&quot; title=&quot;Static compiler doesn&amp;#39;t coerce GString for getAt() call&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-6668&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-6668&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=paulk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;paulk&quot;&gt;paulk&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jwagenleitner&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jwagenleitner&quot;&gt;jwagenleitner&lt;/a&gt; We should discuss &quot;Least Surprise  VS  Strict Type Check&quot; seriously in mailing list.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.CompileStatic

@CompileStatic
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Static {

  def main() {
    meth(1.0d)  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// works
&lt;/span&gt;  }

  def meth(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; val) {
  }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17782655" author="emilles" created="Fri, 3 Nov 2023 16:26:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/ccdd40b2d147c5ce6466f4fd83f84ad164dcfaed&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/ccdd40b2d147c5ce6466f4fd83f84ad164dcfaed&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
